## Open with the problem, not the product

First paragraph earns the read. State the tension a reader feels before they
know we have an answer. No "In this post we will…".

## Use real headings

Markdown / MDX renders to rich text (h2–h4, lists, blockquotes, links, inline
`code`). Fenced code blocks are syntax-highlighted with Shiki in both themes:

```ts
// real, runnable snippets only — no pseudo-code
const span = await store.query({ traceId: "abc123" });
```

- Bullet lists work
- So do [internal links](/start) and external links

> Pull-quotes via blockquote for the one line you want remembered.

## Close with a next step

End with one concrete action: try the sandbox, read the related post, join the
waitlist. Related posts are auto-selected by shared `tags`.
